        "x": 0,
        "y": 27
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Every PVC is bind-/NFS-mounted onto one of **two physical backends**: the **NFS tank pool** (`10.0.10.20:/mnt/tank`, ~30 TB) and the **node's local disk** (`local-path`, ~3.85 TB). `kubelet_volume_stats_*` reports the *backing filesystem*, so all PVCs on a backend report identical capacity/used/free \u2014 summing them (as a naive PVC dashboard does) massively inflates totals. This view deduplicates to the two real backends. True per-PVC usage needs `kube_state_metrics` + a node/NFS exporter, which aren't scraped yet."
      }
    },
