      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "MinIO and the standalone Redis expose rich native Prometheus metrics (`minio_*` bucket/object/IO stats, `redis_*` ops/memory/clients) but they are **not currently scraped** \u2014 so these sections report CPU, memory, disk-I/O and network from cAdvisor. Their data *size* isn't shown because their PVCs sit on the shared backends above (`kubelet_volume_stats` can't isolate a single PVC's usage). Enabling those exporters (MinIO's `/minio/v2/metrics/cluster`, a redis-exporter sidecar) would unlock per-engine detail. Immich's Postgres (CNPG) and Valkey live on the **Immich** dashboard."
